# English-Only Repository Content

From 2026-07-16 onward, **all new and edited repository content must be English**:

- Documentation (`README*`, `CHANGELOG`, `AUDIT`, `SECURITY`, `AGENTS`, `CONTRIBUTING`, ADRs, `.notes/`, PR/issue bodies)
- Code comments, JSDoc/TSDoc, commit messages, CI workflow `name`/`run` echo text
- Default / fallback user-facing strings in new code (e.g. `AppError.toUserMessage()`)
- Cursor rules (`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`, `.cursor/index.mdc`) — write rule bodies in English

## Exceptions (keep as-is unless deliberately migrating)

- Existing `src/i18n/translations.ts` **German locale values** (product i18n)
- Historical CHANGELOG entries already published
- Third-party license text

## Agent / contributor behavior

- Prefer English for PR titles/bodies and review comments on this repo.
- Do not add new German prose to docs or default error strings; use i18n keys when the UI must show DE.

<example>
`throw new AppError({ code: 'NO_API_KEY', message: 'Configure your Gemini API key in Settings.' })`
</example>

<example type="invalid">
`// Bitte API-Key in den Einstellungen setzen` in a new service file
</example>
